  "lyrics": "[Music] Gotta get to bed The bed is getting late That story's just gonna have to wait I get some sleep Everything's alright Your mom and I just have a little fight And now I'll... all from wonder... about the fear he most... I felt... when he... He heard his parents thunder rattle the gates of hell Gotta get up. We're running late. You're some money you're lunch we couldn't make Have a good day Everything's all around Do your best we'll see it tonight Now I'm off and wonder When he heard his parents thunder rattle the game All the gates of hell But long ago, I'd farther away I remember when those starboard days When I film the blame Try to carry the fault Too many ziz followers I have to fall I found some peace of mind on a Sunday Believing the choices I made were at And I'm praying that those troubles last by Monday will be dry I found some peace of mind on this Sunday Leaving the choices and maybe we'll write But I will always wonder I'm about the fear he most felt His parents thunder, rattle the gates of hell. ► ►",
  "lyricsSegments": [
    {
      "end": 12,
      "text": "[Music]",
      "start": 0
    },
    {
      "end": 23.5,
      "text": "Gotta get to bed",
      "start": 11.5
    },
    {
      "end": 35,
      "text": "The bed is getting late That story's just gonna have to wait I get some sleep",
      "start": 23
    },
    {
      "end": 46.5,
      "text": "Everything's alright Your mom and I just have a little fight",
      "start": 34.5
    },
    {
      "end": 58,
      "text": "And now I'll... all from wonder... about the fear he most... I felt... when he...",
      "start": 46
    },
    {
      "end": 69.5,
      "text": "He heard his parents thunder rattle the gates of hell",
      "start": 57.5
    },
    {
      "end": 81,
      "text": "Gotta get up. We're running late.",
      "start": 69
    },
    {
      "end": 92.5,
      "text": "You're some money you're lunch we couldn't make Have a good day Everything's all around",
      "start": 80.5
    },
    {
      "end": 104,
      "text": "Do your best we'll see it tonight Now I'm off and wonder",
      "start": 92
    },
    {
      "end": 115.5,
      "text": "When he heard his parents thunder rattle the game",
      "start": 103.5
    },
    {
      "end": 127,
      "text": "All the gates of hell",
      "start": 115
    },
    {
      "end": 138.5,
      "text": "But long ago, I'd farther away I remember when those starboard days",
      "start": 126.5
    },
    {
      "end": 161.5,
      "text": "When I film the blame Try to carry the fault Too many ziz followers I have to fall",
      "start": 149.5
    },
    {
      "end": 173,
      "text": "I found some peace of mind on a Sunday Believing the choices I made were at",
      "start": 161
    },
    {
      "end": 184.5,
      "text": "And I'm praying that those troubles last by Monday will be dry",
      "start": 172.5
    },
    {
      "end": 196,
      "text": "I found some peace of mind on this Sunday Leaving the choices and maybe we'll write",
      "start": 184
    },
    {
      "end": 207.5,
      "text": "But I will always wonder I'm about the fear he most felt",
      "start": 195.5
    },
    {
      "end": 219,
      "text": "His parents thunder, rattle the gates of hell.",
      "start": 207
    },
